1. Purpose

The Oreulius Community License is intended to support:
	•	research
	•	education
	•	evaluation
	•	benchmarking
	•	security review
	•	non-commercial experimentation
	•	public technical discussion
	•	community contributions

while reserving commercial deployment, commercial hosting, and product
integration rights for separate written agreements with the Licensor.

The goal of this license is to allow the system to be studied, evaluated,
tested, and improved by the community while preserving the ability to
commercialize the software responsibly.

⸻

2. Definitions

“Software”
The Oreulius kernel, source code, documentation, build artifacts, and any
associated materials distributed under this License.

“Licensor”
Keefe Reeves and any project maintainers authorized to manage licensing of
Oreulius.

“You”
Any individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.

“Contributor”
Any person or entity that submits code, documentation, or other modifications
to the Software.

“Commercial Use”
Any use of the Software that directly or indirectly generates revenue,
supports a commercial offering, or is deployed as part of a commercial
product, service, or operational environment.

⸻

