These rights are granted solely for non-commercial purposes unless a
separate commercial agreement is obtained.

⸻

4. Evaluation and Internal Review by Commercial Entities

Commercial organizations may use the Software internally for:
	•	evaluation
	•	benchmarking
	•	interoperability testing
	•	security review
	•	academic or technical research
	•	internal prototype development

provided that the Software is not used in production and is not offered
as part of any commercial product or service.

Internal evaluation must not involve:
	•	revenue-generating deployment
	•	customer-facing services
	•	hosted offerings
	•	operational infrastructure

⸻

5. Non-Commercial Use

You may use and distribute the Software without additional permission for:
	•	personal projects
	•	hobby or experimental systems work
	•	academic research
	•	educational use
	•	open research collaborations
	•	conference demonstrations
	•	public technical exploration
	•	non-commercial prototypes

Non-commercial use does not include:
	•	production use by a commercial entity
	•	paid hosted services
	•	commercial SaaS platforms
	•	revenue-generating deployments
	•	consulting offerings where the Software is a material component
	•	embedding the Software into commercial products or services

⸻

6. Commercial Use

Commercial use requires a separate written agreement with the Licensor.

Commercial use includes, but is not limited to:
	•	incorporating the Software into a commercial product
	•	running the Software in production for a commercial entity
	•	offering hosted or managed services based on the Software
	•	embedding the Software into proprietary systems
	•	distributing the Software as part of a paid platform
	•	providing paid support or consulting where the Software is central to the offering

